      "content": "It is a very common feeling to feel like a ghost when you are so immersed in digital communication that you forget the physical reality of your presence, but you are definitely not a ghost; you are just a human who has temporarily forgotten how to speak to another human being, and that is a very human thing to do. When you are typing instead of talking, it's easy to feel disconnected, but the connection is still there, just in a different format, and speaking out loud can help ground you in the real world again. Sometimes, taking a break from the screen and just talking to yourself or a loved one can bring you back from the edge of the digital void.",
